cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SD 

This paper is about generating polite dialogue responses, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The paper presents three weakly-supervised models for generating polite (or rude) responses without parallel data, which suggests that it could be categorized under machine learning (ML) as well. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which is focused on NLP and ML for language-related tasks. The paper also uses reinforcement learning, which could place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves generating diverse responses, which could be related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.SD (Software Engineering).
